HEADWORD: Rebuttal
<hw>Re*but"tal</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*b⟦ucr⟧t"t⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The giving of evidence on the part of a plaintiff
to destroy the effect of evidence introduced by the defendant in the
same suit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

